# Checkwright drift-kit KPI registry — drift-kit/SPEC.md §The report skeleton.
# One plugin name per line, # comments (the gates.list grammar). Names resolve
# against scripts/ first, then each vendored kit's kpis/. Advisory: the report
# never joins gates.list; it feeds the session-context trend line.

# Lead — weighted high; act before drift compounds.
kpi-task-split
kpi-gate-backlog
kpi-amendment-age
kpi-deferred-age
kpi-prompt-friction
kpi-always-loaded
kpi-settings-local
kpi-gate-runtime
kpi-overhead
kpi-price-table-age

# Lag — weighted low; undercounts by construction. kpi-knowledge-friction reads
# drift-kit's knowledge-friction loop (its capture convention + close triage);
# n/a until this iteration's log has an entry.
kpi-knowledge-friction
